			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				You could simply backup your databases, uninstall and reinstall the RPM file for MySQL and then restore your DB's.   Redhat is quite simple to repair using the RPMS.
<br />

<br />
I can help you with this if you want Cobee.  Just IM me or email me.
<br />

<br />
also, you might want to use apt-get for updates now.. since the up2date part of RedHat is only good until April 30th, 2004.  They ported the debian apt-get to use RPMS and stuff.   <a href="http://apt.freshrpms.net." target="_blank">http://apt.freshrpms.net.</a>   I can help with that also.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
