			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				You should always create a second account with the same privilages as the root account, just for such an occasion, and also shouldn't use the ROOT account for your DB access.
<br />

<br />
You could just use the --skip-grant-tables option and do a INSERT into the 'user' table to fix it.  instead of using mysqladmin.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
